# GSH LlamaCloud + Motia Integration Project Overview

## 🎯 Project Mission

This project integrates **LlamaCloud** with **Motia** to create an intelligent
**GSH (Good Samaritan Hospital)** behavioral health document analysis and
workflow automation system.

## 🏥 Healthcare Context

- **Domain**: Behavioral Health Services Management
- **Client**: Good Samaritan Hospital (GSH)
- **Compliance**: HIPAA-compliant data handling required
- **Sensitivity**: Healthcare data requires heightened security measures

## 🏗️ Core Architecture Stack

- **Workflow Engine**: [Motia](https://www.motia.dev) - Event-driven TypeScript
  framework
- **AI/Document Processing**: [LlamaCloud](https://cloud.llamaindex.ai) -
  Enterprise document analysis
- **Graph Database**: [Neo4j](mdc:docker-compose.yml) with MCP integration
- **Task Management**: [Task system](mdc:tasks/README.md) with 4-phase
  implementation
- **Containerization**: Docker for Neo4j and MCP servers

## 📋 Current Project Status

- ✅ **Complete codebase analysis**: [repomix-output.md](mdc:repomix-output.md)
  (318KB)
- ✅ **Task documentation**: Comprehensive 4-phase plan in [tasks/](mdc:tasks/)
- ✅ **Infrastructure setup**: Neo4j, MCP servers, Docker configuration
- 🔄 **Phase 1 Ready**: Foundation setup for LlamaCloud integration

## 🎯 Primary Objectives

1. **Document Intelligence**: Process GSH behavioral health documents using
   LlamaCloud
2. **Code-Document Correlation**: Link existing codebase with project
   requirements
3. **Workflow Automation**: Create Motia-powered analysis and reporting
   workflows
4. **Knowledge Management**: Store insights in Neo4j graph database
5. **Gap Analysis**: Identify implementation gaps and generate recommendations

## 📊 Key Success Metrics

- Integration of 318KB codebase with LlamaCloud indexing
- Processing of [ALL-GOOD-SAM-DOCS/](mdc:ALL-GOOD-SAM-DOCS/) healthcare
  documents
- Automated workflow generation for document analysis
- Real-time insights and recommendation system

